Personal Interest

This project excites me because I'm an avid reader but I have poor management skiils, building a tool I'll use daily provides an incentive to keep reading

The scalability is open ended as this class project can be turned into something with real users and ongoing development.

The technical challenges from database optimization to recommendation can improve skills and prepare me for professional software development roles.

============================================================================

Timeline 

Weeks 1-3: Database design, API planning, UI wireframes, and development environment setup.

Weeks 4-7: Backend development including authentication, book management, and reading tracker functionality.

Weeks 8-11: Frontend development with React components, book search interface, and user profiles.

Weeks 12-14: Social features, recommendation system, statistics dashboard, and book lists.

Weeks 15-16: Testing, bug fixes, deployment, and presentation preparation.

This timeline includes buffer time for unexpected challenges while ensuring steady progress with demonstrable milestones.
